SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR 
a) Since C is horizontally stretched compared to one graph B and
compressed compared to others (D and A), it should be \( \ f(x) \).
$BR $SPACE $BR
b) The most horizontally stretched of the graphs are A and D, so
they should be \( \ f \left( \frac{1}{2} x \right) \) and \( \ f \left( - \frac{1}{2} x \right) \).  Since D appears to be a
compressed version of C which is NOT reflected across the $BITALIC y${EITALIC}-axis, it should be \( \ f \left( \frac{1}{2} x \right) \).  
$BR $SPACE $BR
c) The most horizontally compressed of the graphs should be \( \ f(-2x) \), which is B.  Notice this graph is also a reflection of the graph of \( \ f(x) \) $SPACE ( graph C) about the $BITALIC y${EITALIC}-axis.  
$BR $SPACE $BR
d) The most horizontally stretched of the graphs are A and D, so
they should be \( \ f \left( \frac{1}{2} x \right) \) and \( \ f \left( - \frac{1}{2} x \right) \).  Since A appears to be a
compressed version of C which is reflected across the $BITALIC y${EITALIC}-axis, it should be \( \ f \left( - \frac{1}{2} x \right) \).  
$BR
END_SOLUTION

